        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: \"Your medical history: 6 critical categories of information to share with your doctor | UT MD Anderson\"\nurl: \"https://www.mdanderson.org/cancerwise/what-constitutes-your-medical-history.h00-159460845.html\"\ndescription: \"Also tell your doctor about any major surgical procedures you’ve had, especially if you experienced serious complications, such as a reaction to anesthesia or excessive bleeding.\"\npage_age: \"\"\nprofile_name: MD Anderson Cancer Center\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/cEx36IR4bzabuJyepUtb7ESBQquR9-DYHtdGFGSTZ-0/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvNGNhMTE2Y2I1/N2Y2YmQxMzEwZmE4/ZTMwZWI1M2NmZGIx/MzM5N2RjMTFiOGU2/ZGIzOTE1NDNiMGUw/ZGUxMmVjNS93d3cu/bWRhbmRlcnNvbi5v/cmcv\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/QkEx4frjcQeaM--MlpNy_AJY06fUAq49ZZBfyr8reNo/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/bWRhbmRlcnNvbi5v/cmcvY2FuY2Vyd2lz/ZS8yMDIxLzA1L3do/YXQtY29uc3RpdHV0/ZXMteW91ci1tZWRp/Y2FsLWhpc3Rvcnkv/amNyOmNvbnRlbnQv/YmxvZy9hZGFwdGl2/ZWltYWdlLnJlc2l6/ZS43MDIuNDA0Lmpw/Zw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://www.mdanderson.org/cancerwise/2021/05/what-constitutes-your-medical-history/jcr:content/blog/adaptiveimage.resize.702.404.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"That’s because everything from the aftermath of childhood diseases to the side effects of current medications can influence which treatments you’re offered for new conditions and how effective they might be. But what actually makes up your “medical history,” and what are the most critical things to share with your doctor?|Any time you see a new doctor, one of the first things they’ll ask about is your medical history.|Also tell your doctor about any major surgical procedures you’ve had, especially if you experienced serious complications, such as a reaction to anesthesia or excessive bleeding.|Here are six things she wants every cancer patient to share with their doctors. ... Some cancer patients may think that if their diabetes or high blood pressure is well-controlled – whether through medication or lifestyle choices – then they don’t even need to bring it up.\"\nhash: 06ffddd14a43eb3f\nembed_ref: mdanderson.org-2E8\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
