        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: Prepare for Your Initial Doctor Visit | Medical Board of California\nurl: \"https://www.mbc.ca.gov/Resources/Medical-Resources/doctor-visit.aspx\"\ndescription: \"An online library of the Board's various forms, publications, brochures, alerts, statistics, and medical resources. Contact the Board's Consumer Information Unit for assistance. Toll Free: (800) 633-2322 Send a message to request help · Before your initial visit to a new doctor, make a list of things you want to tell him or her about your health history.\"\npage_age: \"\"\nprofile_name: CA\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/FKpr8xD2gz5C-SL8dXx5ixA36a1wafdBgsumLeedOoY/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvNDI5YTc4MWVm/ZTFiMDBiYmYwMzkx/YzY4NDdkMTA1NzFh/NzZkMGNhMjQ5NmVh/MTQyNjI3YzE1YzA4/MDkyMDE1Yi93d3cu/bWJjLmNhLmdvdi8\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/au25f1RSy4cSgmaTm1lS0BR__SQnfPJob2wNRh-CUqw/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/bWJjLmNhLmdvdi9p/bWFnZXMvc29jaWFs/L01CQy1oZC53ZWJw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://www.mbc.ca.gov/images/social/MBC-hd.webp\"\nextra_snippets: \"An online library of the Board's various forms, publications, brochures, alerts, statistics, and medical resources. Contact the Board's Consumer Information Unit for assistance. Toll Free: (800) 633-2322 Send a message to request help · Before your initial visit to a new doctor, make a list of things you want to tell him or her about your health history.|special training the doctor may have in managing any medical conditions you have (such as diabetes, heart disease, high blood pressure, etc.)|You should feel that you were treated courteously, that all your questions were answered, and that you were not rushed or dismissed. Your relationship with a doctor is one of the most intimate in life; you should be able to trust him or her with the most private situations or problems, and should feel that your doctor is your ally.|After the initial visit, if you are satisfied with what you experienced, great. If not, remember the choice is yours. Try another doctor.\"\nhash: ba9fd05fa4b6d65b\nembed_ref: mbc.ca.gov-ZQp\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
