        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: 10 Useful Types of Medical Information to Bring to a New PCP\nurl: \"https://betterhealthwhileaging.net/10-types-medical-information-for-new-doctor-or-phr/\"\ndescription: Emergency room clinical note. This is the note dictated (or typed) by the emergency room doctor who managed your loved one’s visit. Hospital Admission History & Physical.\npage_age: \"July 24, 2025\"\nprofile_name: Better Health While Aging\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/v61xzNVmsU4x_ADCiXqBlqZixQt50WBhZj193iitJl8/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMTA1NzQ2ZjRk/MjI1YzJiYmViNWM0/N2YyZTI3MDljYjM5/OWVhOGQ2ZTYyODkw/OWU3MmI4NDkxNjc0/YWIzYTYwMy9iZXR0/ZXJoZWFsdGh3aGls/ZWFnaW5nLm5ldC8\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/4JVJeMcTO9h_-38BadmgYDCZOnhby3k16MPIOH6GJCs/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9iZXR0/ZXJoZWFsdGh3aGls/ZWFnaW5nLm5ldC93/cC1jb250ZW50L3Vw/bG9hZHMvMjAxNC8w/OC9iaWdzdG9jay1N/ZWRpY2FsLVJlY29y/ZC03NzAyODc3LTMw/MHgyMDAuanBn\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://betterhealthwhileaging.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/bigstock-Medical-Record-7702877-300x200.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"Emergency room clinical note. This is the note dictated (or typed) by the emergency room doctor who managed your loved one’s visit. Hospital Admission History & Physical.|Do you have to bring this information? Of course not. In my own experience, most people bring nothing more than a medication list, if that. And they leave it to the new doctors to request health information from the previous doctors, which often arrives well after that first new patient visit.|But occasionally, a new patient would come with useful health information in hand. This generally made a big difference in how quickly we could ensure that our new patient was getting the right medical care from us, and from other involved doctors.|This list is especially suited to the primary care of aging adults with chronic medical problems. But most of this information can come in handy for first visits with specialists. It can also be very useful to clinicians in the emergency room, or at urgent care. Note: If you or your loved one have been maintaining a personal health record, this is the type of information that I hope you’ve been keeping in your personal health record! This would include any conditions that you currently see a doctor for, or is being monitored.\"\nhash: adb77ef58b06ab5a\nembed_ref: betterhealthwhileaging.net-6Tf\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
