        "embed_id": "093cce1e-f9ca-4e58-9422-14764f959429",
        "type": "website",
        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: Talking With Your Doctor Worksheets | National Institute on Aging\nurl: \"https://www.nia.nih.gov/health/medical-care-and-appointments/talking-your-doctor-worksheets\"\ndescription: \"For your convenience, use these worksheets to organize your questions, family and medical history, and information when talking with your doctor. You can download, print, and copy the worksheets. A family medical history can identify people with a higher-than-usual chance of having common disorders, such as heart disease, diabetes, and more. This form can help you organize your thoughts about conditions and illnesses that have affected your family members. View Worksheet 1: Family Health History (PDF, 107K) Use this worksheet to answer some questions for, and about, a new doctor you are considering.\"\npage_age: \"January 26, 2026\"\nprofile_name: National Institute on Aging\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/7w-QJkOvnMro34sTl9v25MRxqOhnRnPPlOo18EjUKjc/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMjEzY2Q0YjEz/YzBmOTVjZTI4NTZm/NzA1ZjZmYzhhMDg4/ZjFmODE3MWQyMTA3/ZTcwZDI3NWQzNmE1/NWY2NDM4Zi93d3cu/bmlhLm5paC5nb3Yv\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/UerSFYK4MBH2dK5ZW5e5lXk7PtYBhPVe9VnmGtiPlqA/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/bmlhLm5paC5nb3Yv/dGhlbWVzL25pYS9p/bWFnZXMvdGh1bWJf/YXJ0aWNsZV9vZy5q/cGc\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://www.nia.nih.gov/themes/nia/images/thumb_article_og.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"For your convenience, use these worksheets to organize your questions, family and medical history, and information when talking with your doctor. You can download, print, and copy the worksheets. A family medical history can identify people with a higher-than-usual chance of having common disorders, such as heart disease, diabetes, and more. This form can help you organize your thoughts about conditions and illnesses that have affected your family members. View Worksheet 1: Family Health History (PDF, 107K) Use this worksheet to answer some questions for, and about, a new doctor you are considering.|It's important to tell your doctor about any changes in your life since your last appointment. Use this worksheet to help you record what you want to discuss with your doctor during your next visit. ... Use this form to help organize your thoughts about any health or other concerns you want to discuss with your doctor. ... This worksheet can help you keep track of different medicines, including vitamins, over-the-counter drugs, and prescriptions.\"\nhash: 1d627430d14a6cfc\nembed_ref: nia.nih.gov-Ufy\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
